<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CE 200, CE 300 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - REMOVE - Steering Wheel / Clock Spring</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="13">
        <title>Steering Wheel / Clock Spring</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always disconnect power source before working on electrical equipment.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Front and Side Cover</title>
            <figure id="f0900956" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900956.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Steering Wheel Front Cover</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FRONT COVER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">The steering wheel removal process is intended for the removal of the component parts
                    of the steering wheel assembly. Special note should be taken in the steering wheel mounted switches.
                    Depending on municipality requirements the steering wheel switch options may vary.
                </emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900957" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900957.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="288px"/>
                <caption>Figure 66. Releasing Front Cover With Tool</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To release front cover, insert removal tool (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900957">Figure 66</hotlnk>) into aperture. Phillips head screwdriver may be used.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>2. Push inward to release steering wheel cover retaining clips (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900960">Figure 69, Item 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900958" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900958.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 67. Removing Cover</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grasp cover as shown (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900958">Figure 67</hotlnk>). Lift cover from steering wheel assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900959" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900959.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 68. Side Cover Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TURN SIGNAL SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SIDE COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RETAINING SCREW</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the steering column cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900959">Figure 68, Item 3</hotlnk>) fastener openings on the underside of steering
                    wheel covers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert Phillips head screwdriver in cover opening, loosen Phillips head screw and
                    remove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove side covers.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Locking Clip</title>
            <figure id="f0900960" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900960.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 69. Locking Clip</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOCKING CLIPS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0900961" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900961.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 70. Steering Wheel Retaining Nut</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. STEERING WHEEL RETAINING NUT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the retaining nut from the shaft spindle (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900961.webp">Figure 70, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the harness section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900962.webp">Figure 71, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900962" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900962.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 71. Steering Wheel Harness Disconnect</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. STEERING WHEEL HARNESS CONNECTION</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Steering Wheel</title>
            <figure id="f0900963" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900963.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 72. Mark Shaft and Spindle Alignment</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MARK LOCATION FOR REALIGNMENT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make a corresponding mark on the shaft spindle and plate to aid alignment in
                    reassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900964" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900964.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                         scalefitheight="288px"/>
                <caption>Figure 73. Utilizing Wheel Puller to Remove Steering Wheel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WHEEL PULLER MOUNTED ON STEERING WHEEL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a wheel puller (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900964">Figure 73, Item 1</hotlnk>) to loosen steering wheel from shaft spindle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove steering wheel from spindle.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Clock Spring</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Follow the installation instructions printed on the clock spring to avoid damage.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0900965" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900965.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 74. Clock Spring</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CLOCK SPRING BODY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CLOCK SPRING HARNESS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPINDLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the clock spring harness from the dash harness (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900967">Figure 76, Item 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900966" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900966.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 75. Clock Spring Harness and Attachment Tabs</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CLOCK SPRING ATTACHMENT TABS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CLOCK SPRING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. CLOCK SPRING HARNESS CONNECTION</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove Phillips head screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900966">Figure 75, Item 1</hotlnk>) from tabs.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift clock spring out to remove.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900967" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900967.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 76. Clock Spring Assembly With Harness</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CLOCK SPRING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CLOCK SPRING HARNESS PIG TAIL</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DASH HARNESS CONNECTION</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Door Switch and Flasher Light Modules</title>
            <para>The switch modules in the steering wheel assembly are easily removed. The left hand switch module
                controls the opening and closing of the side passenger entry door. The right side switch module controls
                the amber flasher and red override switch.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900968" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900968.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 77. Steering Wheel Switch Modules Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MODULE DIRECTION FOR REMOVAL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the switch modules from the steering wheel, slide them toward the center (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900968">Figure 77</hotlnk>) of the steering wheel assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
